locality: Manti-La Sal National Forest. F.S. road 027 west out of Wales, Utah until you encounter F.S. 157. Go South on F.S. 157 until you encounter a large saddle. To the East of the saddle you will find a large dead juniper that has has the upper portion cut off. Just a few steps East of the Juniper is a large rock that is being used for this site.
By Hidden Valley Park in Sandy Utah, along the Bonneville Shoreline hiking trail facing west in a partly shaded area of scrub oaks on a granite rock.

Up Big Cottonwood canyon. Entering Storm mountain campground headed toward the amphitheater. Following the trail past the amphitheater the hike gains elevation and makes a small loop until you are above the campground. On this ridge there are many sedimentary layered rocks with various lichens species living there.

Manti-La Sal National Forest. Take highway 89 at Thistle junction heading South. At the bottom of the hill take F.S. rd 070 until you encounter the forest service boundary sign. as you cross the guard rail at the boundary sign to the west 100 ft against the fence you will see a very large boulder. The boulder is the site of lichen study.
